{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"StaticRWLock","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Take a look at the following example:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["  GStaticRWLock rwlock = G_STATIC_RW_LOCK_INIT;","  GPtrArray *array;","","  gpointer","  my_array_get (guint index)","  {","    gpointer retval = NULL;","","    if (!array)","      return NULL;","","    g_static_rw_lock_reader_lock (&rwlock);","    if (index < array->len)","      retval = g_ptr_array_index (array, index);","    g_static_rw_lock_reader_unlock (&rwlock);","","    return retval;","  }","","  void","  my_array_set (guint index, gpointer data)","  {","    g_static_rw_lock_writer_lock (&rwlock);","","    if (!array)","      array = g_ptr_array_new ();","","    if (index >= array->len)","      g_ptr_array_set_size (array, index + 1);","    g_ptr_array_index (array, index) = data;","","    g_static_rw_lock_writer_unlock (&rwlock);","  }"],"syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example shows an array which can be accessed by many readers"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(the "},{"code":"my_array_get()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function) simultaneously, whereas the writers","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"my_array_set()"},{"type":"text","text":" function) will only be allowed once at a time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and only if no readers currently access the array. This is because","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of the potentially dangerous resizing of the array. Using these"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions is fully multi-thread safe now."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Most of the time, writers should have precedence over readers. That","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"means, for this implementation, that as soon as a writer wants to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"lock the data, no other reader is allowed to lock the data, whereas,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of course, the readers that already have locked the data are allowed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to finish their operation. As soon as the last reader unlocks the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"data, the writer will lock it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even though "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is not opaque, it should only be used"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with the following functions."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the g_static_rw_lock_* functions can be used even if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" has not been called. Then they do nothing, apart"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"from g_static_rw_lock_*_trylock, which does nothing but returning ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A read-write lock has a higher overhead than a mutex. For example, both"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_rw_lock_reader_lock()"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_rw_lock_reader_unlock()"},{"text":" have","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to lock and unlock a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", so it takes at least twice the time","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to lock and unlock a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" that it does to lock and unlock a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","type":"reference"},{"text":". So only data structures that are accessed by multiple","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"readers, and which keep the lock for a considerable time justify a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":". The above example most probably would fare better with a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying "},{"code":"GStaticRWLock","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a strong reference or owner of a "},{"code":"GStaticRWLock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLockRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"code":"GStaticRWLock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}],"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note"}]}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Class","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"StaticRWLock","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"StaticRWLock","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticRWLock"}],"symbolKind":"class","externalID":"s:4GLib12StaticRWLockC"},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock"},{"text":" struct represents a read-write lock. A read-write","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lock can be used for protecting data that some portions of code only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"read from, while others also write. In such situations it is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"desirable that several readers can read at once, whereas of course"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"only one writer may write at a time."}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(_:)-33hto","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(_:)-3kcsg","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticRWLock\/init(_:)-3z